                            <comment id="14431939" author="rfscholte" created="Sat, 30 Mar 2013 13:56:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed in &lt;a href=&quot;http://svn.apache.org/r1462841&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;r1462841&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
I&apos;ve added a test, nothing special there with borders.&lt;br/&gt;
Borders are more of a browser and/or cascading stylesheet issue, don&apos;t think we can or should fix it here.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14432213" author="dennisl@apache.org" created="Mon, 1 Apr 2013 16:01:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for fixing part of this Robert.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I agree that borders are best handled with cascading style sheets. The problem is that the xhtml code that is generated by the above APT snippet adds &lt;tt&gt;border=&quot;1&quot;&lt;/tt&gt; to the &lt;tt&gt;table&amp;gt;&lt;/tt&gt; element. I think it would be better to not have this attribute generated.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="18005671" author="sparsick" created="Tue, 15 Jul 2025 09:58:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This project has moved from Jira to GitHub Issues. This issue was migrated to &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/maven-doxia/issues/396&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;apache/maven-doxia#396&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
